Text: In ancient times, the Goddess Beatrix...

bestowed power upon the hero, Olivier, so that she
might defeat the demon, Diablos.

Olivier met Diablos in battle with dauntless valor
and is said to have sealed the fiend's left arm
within the Sanctuary before it could vanish.

Even now, the warriors of old who stood beside
Olivier in this most holy conflict await you all
beyond these very doors!
Yaaah!!!
You all know what it is these brave souls seek.
Yes, the path of righteousness...
(I don't like this man...)
(The Archbishop Jack Nelson...)
This grumble passes through Alexia's mind.

She watches the opening ceremony of the Goddess'
Trial from the VIP section.

Seated on either side of Alexia are Natsume and
Rose.

While there are many other esteemed people seated in
the rows behind them, they are the guests of honor.

They are obviously being used to draw a larger crowd
by being pretty girls on display, but that isn't
really the issue.
No, there are two things that Alexia finds irksome.
The firstãƒ¼

She does not like Nelson, the acting archbishop,
who is droning on so pompously in the middle
of the arena.

(That baldheaded cretin could at least pretend to be
in mourning.)

What do you mean, you're rescinding your acceptance of
an investigation?!

Alexia spoke with Nelson about the murder of the
archbishop, but he adamantly refused to let her
investigate the incident.

It all started with his absurd assertion that the
matter was concluded since the subject of the
investigation was dead.

Alexia had diplomatically told Nelson that he was a
fool for not seeing that it was all the more reason
to hold an investigation.

But the acting archbishop had held fast to his demand
she get her request reapproved.
I'm terribly sorry...

But as my esteemed guest can see, the archbishop,
who had been the object of so much scrutiny in the
capital as of late, has met a truly sorrowful end.

We of the Church must apprehend the blackguard
responsible for this barbaric act at once.

There is also the urgent matter of seeing that the
Goddess' Trial goes forward without a hitch, so I'm
afraid I haven't the time to indulge "Your Royal
Highness" in this...
...Oh, do forgive my manners.

At any rate, I ask that you please allow the Church
to handle Church matters, as we have in the past!

I shall submit a report to His Royal Highness
personally, so all you need concern yourself
with, Princess Alexia,
is enjoying the Goddess' Trial.

(But even if I were to rush back to the capital and
persuade Father to grant permission for another
Crimson Order investigation...)

(Does this dolt realize how many days that would take
round-trip?!)

(Every crucial piece of evidence would go missing
in the meantime, I just know it!)

(Still, I can't very well risk worsening relations
with the Church by forcing the inquiry to go
through...)

(Any strong-arm tactics here could result in pressure
from neighboring lands, too.)

The biggest issue would be the loss of support among
the masses. Religions make useful allies, but also
the most grievous of enemies.

(That bald creep is so obviously suspicious!
Ugh, I REALLY don't like this!)
Natsume!!!
We love you, Natsume!!!
Ahaha!
(Speaking of things I don't like...)

Alexia lets out a long sigh, giving this Natsume or
whatever her name is the side eye.
She is the other thing that is annoying Alexia here.
Thank you all so much for your support!

(Natsume Kafka. Seems she's the belle of the literary
ball at the moment...)

While Alexia can't say anything toward claims that
this "Natsume" is a once-in-a-millennium genius
novelist, the fact stands that before today she had
never even heard of her.

Part of this is probably due to Alexia not having a
shred of interest in literature,

but being a princess, she tries to remember the more
famous authors.
(Flawless behavior.)

(A presence that belies being a newcomer to
the scene.)

It all smells like an act. But this is not jealousy.
If anything, it is a case of disliking someone
so similar to herself.

Alexia also behaves impeccably when greeting the
general public.

She has lived her whole life suppressing her inner
self and playing the part of the perfect princess.

Everyone at the top has a role to act out, big or
small, but few have it in them to hold back their
true nature while doing so.
Ahaha!
...Ah, haha!
(...She's so fake.)
...Eheheh!
Whoooahãƒ¼!!
Princess Alexia is the best!
C'mon, everyone!
Let's cheer everyone on together, okay?
Yaaaaah!

That's when Alexia sees itâ€”one of Natsume's cheeks
twitches upward in a smirk.
Heh!
Something snaps within Alexia.

Beta thinks internally as she plays the part of her
novelist alter-ego, Natsume.
(...I can't stand her.)
(Alexia Midgar.)

She doesn't deserve to appear in "The Chronicles of
Master Shadow."

(She's a vile insect who uses her status as princess
and schoolmate to buzz around Master Shadow.)

(Look at her waving and wheedling the crowd with that
gag-inducing voice and phony smile.)

(This model princess act she's putting on is as fake
as can be.)

(As if someone as lacking as her in ability, looks,
love for my lord, and everything else could ever
be such a thing.)

(No, that role belongs to a charming elf with silver
hair and a beauty mark under her blue eyes!)
This is not mere jealousy.

Beta's blood boiled even back when she learned that
Master Shadow had rescued Alexia from her abductor.

(The fact that the part didn't go to meâ€”no, that
this...cheap bimbo dared inconvenience my lord
makes me seethe with rage.)
In order to keep this rage in check,

Beta had rewritten the rescued maiden so that she was
instead a charming silver-haired, blue-eyed elf with
a beauty mark under her blue eyes, re-reading
the scene over and over late into the night.
(People like her are always hateful on the inside.)

(Not that my lord would ever get mixed up with such a
cheap little traâ€”)

A sharp pain suddenly shoots through Beta's right
foot.
Agh!
Owww...

She chokes back a cry and looks down to see Alexia's
heel crushing down on her foot.

Fighting off the feeling of something about to snap
inside herself, she speaks calmly.
L-Lady Alexia...? M-My foot...

Alexia makes no attempt to apologize, and even
smiles, of all things.
Oh, is something the matter?
She grinds her heel even harder into Beta's foot.
M-My...foot!
Y-You...
(You rotten biiiiiiitch!!!)

Beta nearly loses it, but desperately endures while
recalling her loyalty toward her honored lord and
the Shadow Garden.
Ehehe...

Off to the other side, Rose beams happily. She has
been in a wonderful mood all morning.
The time has come!
Oh, great Goddess Beatrix!
Heed our prayers...

...and bestow upon the warriors assembled here their
ordeal!!!
And now...
...let the Goddess' Trial begin!!!
Yaaah!!!
Yaaaaaay!!!
